<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8581> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8581" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 740, footnote 131" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3062> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3062" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent as head of an embassy to Crete to mediate a war between Hierapytna and Itanos (Guarducci, I. Cret. 3.4.9, line 49, and 10, lines 57, 65f.; cf. I. v. Magn. 105, and SIG\n     685, lines 49 and 54) between the death of Ptolemy VI in 145 and the consulship of Laelius in 140." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3014> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3014" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 124, 466f. (Ser. Sulpi[cius- - - -] Galba, L. Aurelius [- - - -]n. Cotta); Fast. Ant., ib. 160f. ([L. A]ureli. Cotta); Liv. Oxy. Per. 52; Val. Max. 6.4.2; Frontin. Aq. 1.7; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. The Consuls contended for the Spanish command but at Scipio's suggestion both were passed over (Val. Max. 6.4.2). On Cotta, see Münzer, APF 320." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2928> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2928" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Continued in command in Farther Spain, where, along with Lucullus, he invaded Lusitania, and after inducing three tribes to surrender he treacherously slew 8000 persons and sold the rest into{457} slavery (App. Ib. 59-61; cf. Cic. Brut. 89; Nep. Cato 3.4; Liv. Oxy. Per. 49; Per. 49; Val. Max. 8.1.2, and 7.1; 9.6.2; Suet. Galba 3.2; Ps.-Ascon. 203 Stangl; Oros. 4.21.10)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2927> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2927" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cicero and Valerius Maximus call him Praetor at the time of the slaughter of the Lusitani, but the event appears to belong to his second year in Spain. Cf. Verres, called Praetor in Sicily, 73-71." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2918> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2918" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He won a battle against Lusitanian invaders, but in the pursuit suffered losses. He wintered at Conistorgis (App. Ib. 58; Liv. Per. 48; Oros. 4.21.3; cf. Cic. Brut. 89; Nepos Cato 3.4; Val. Max. 8.1.2; Suet. Galba 3; Ps.-Ascon. 203 Stangl)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2788> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2788" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Opposed granting Paullus a triumph because of his lack of generosity toward his soldiers (Liv. 45.35.8-9, and 36.2-6, cf. 36.7-39.20; Plut. Aem. 30.2-4, cf. 31-32.1).{435}" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2785> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2785" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably all or almost all the Tribunes of the Soldiers and the Lieutenants who served in Macedonia and Illyria continued until their respective commanders returned." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2748> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2748" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Paullus at Pydna (Liv. 45.35.8; Plut. Aem. 30.3)." .
